<subSubSection id="C33A1BD9FFCDFF86FF1DFF493BAAFE14" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9F4852FFCDFF86FF1DFF493BDAFE8F" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,476]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFCDFF86FF1DFF493838FF79" bold="true" box="[198,343,151,177]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Comments:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFCDFF86FEAFFF463B08FF79" box="[372,615,152,177]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFCDFF86FEAFFF463B08FF79" box="[372,615,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Orthophytum humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFCDFF86FD25FF4639DDFF1F" authority="Wanderley &amp; Conceicao (2006: 4)" authorityName="Wanderley &amp; Conceicao" authorityPageNumber="4" authorityYear="2006" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mucugense">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFCDFF86FD25FF463D4CFF79" box="[766,1059,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Orthophytum mucugense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB135A3FFCDFF86FBF1FF4639DDFF1F" author="Wanderley, M. G. L. &amp; Conceicao, A. A." pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="3 - 8" refId="ref12980" refString="Wanderley, M. G. L. &amp; Conceicao, A. A. (2006) Notas taxonomicas e uma nova especie do genero Orthophytum Beer (Bromeliaceae) da Chapada Diamantina, Bahia, Brasil. Sitientibus Serie Ciencas Biologicas 6: 3 - 8." type="journal article" year="2006">Wanderley &amp; Conceição (2006: 4)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, differing mainly by the leaf blades that are densely lepidote (vs. sparsely lepidote), and prickles that are 
<quantity id="4CD8E5B7FFCDFF86FF4CFF3C3871FF34" box="[151,286,226,252]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0499999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="cm" value="1.0499999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="0.7">0.7–1.4 cm</quantity>
long (vs. 
<quantity id="4CD8E5B7FFCDFF86FE42FF3C3B45FF34" box="[409,554,226,252]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.4 mm</quantity>
long). 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFCDFF86FD58FF3C3A13FF33" box="[643,892,226,251]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFCDFF86FD58FF3C3A13FF33" box="[643,892,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Orthophytum humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFCDFF86FB83FF3C38C5FEEA" authority="Louzada &amp; Wanderley (2008: 406)" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityPageNumber="406" authorityYear="2008" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophiuroides">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFCDFF86FB83FF3C3C62FF33" box="[1112,1293,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">O. ophiuroides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB135A3FFCDFF86FACEFF3C38C5FEEA" author="Louzada, R. B. &amp; Wanderley, M. G. L." pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="405 - 410" refId="ref12255" refString="Louzada, R. B. &amp; Wanderley, M. G. L. (2008) Uma nova especie de Orthophytum Beer (Bromeliaceae) relacionada a Orthophytum navioides (L. B. Sm.) L. B. Sm. Hoehnea 35: 405 - 410." type="journal article" year="2008">Louzada &amp; Wanderley (2008: 406)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated mainly by its simple inflorescence (vs. branched inflorescence) and green coloured sepals and bracts (vs. red).
</paragraph>
